events.description: War of 1812: British soldiers burn Buffalo, New York.

events.description: Filipino patriot and reform advocate José Rizal is executed by a Spanish firing squad in Manila.
events.html: • 1896 – Filipino patriot and reform advocate José Rizal is executed by a Spanish firing squad in Manila.

events.description: A fire at the Iroquois Theater in Chicago, Illinois kills at least 605.

events.description: Former Idaho Governor Frank Steunenberg is assassinated at the front gate of his home in Caldwell.

events.description: Russian mystic and advisor to the Tsar Grigori Yefimovich Rasputin is murdered by a loyalist group led by Prince Felix Yusupov. His frozen, partially-trussed body was discovered in a Petrograd river three days later.
